    <h1 class="text-xl font-semibold">MSAO Facilities</h1> 
    <p>The Miskatonic Southern Antarctic Observatory (MSAO) was open on September 1, 1992 as part of an extension of the Amundsen–Scott South Pole Station. It began being constructed beside other telescope and observatory around 1989, It since has been equip with the state of the art camera and detector and is used to detech any signal from distant galaxy and the void. Overtime, the observatory had manage and upgrade on its equipment.</p>
    <p>The observatory is located 1.4 km north of the Amundsen–Scott South Pole Station. The observatory is equip with a 20 meter telescope and the custom CMB waves camera were later added to detect CMB waves and work in tandem with other CMB array. The facilites is manned by 6 Scientist and Engineer at a time where shifted are established with the Amundsen–Scott South Pole Station. The observatory is equip with back-up power generator, water generator from snow, telecominucation lines with Amundsen–Scott South Pole Station, laboratory, workshop, and a garage.</p>
